		<b>Comment By Mike Shay, 4-10-09</b>
		<p>Proud to be a member in good standing of First Novel in the Basement crowd. And by the look of things, that spring thaw is going to be a whopper. I see hundreds, maybe thousands, of first novels floating out of Boulder and Cheyenne and Billings basements and down Eastern Slope watersheds into the Mighty Mississipp, where they will comingle and and become one gigantic epic novel which will soak up all the water, clog the waterway somewhere near New Orleans and be declared the nation's largest navigational hazard. People will be clamoring to read our waterlogged prose. Or string us up. At long last, all of us basement novel authors will be featured on cable news.</p>
		
		<b>Comment By Jill Kuraitis, 4-11-09</b>
